This paper discusses the construction of neighborhood graphs, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the application of the method to continuous domains such as images, signals, and texts, which suggests that it could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
